result.execSummary:
The disposition of "Other" is used to indicate several different dispositions. The Charge(s)/Sentence(s) and Court Record Events sections of the WCCA record display additional information that must be reviewed in order to determine the exact disposition of the charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jozef Handzel in court with attorney Gabriela A. Leija.  Jesica Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for return on doctor's report. Court reviewed the report with the parties. Neither party is challenging the report. Court accepts findings of Dr. Lundbohm and finds the defendant is not competent but likely to regain competency. Court endorsed recommendation of Dr. Lundbohm and ordered the defendant to participate in the Outpatient Competency Restoration Program (OCRP). Court ordered proceedings SUSPENDED. Order for Commitment of Treatment signed and filed. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for June 1, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jozef Handzel in court with attorney Gabriela A. Leija.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense raising competency.  State does not object to have an out-of-custody forensic evaluation. Based on representation of counsel court will order a Competency evaluation.

Defendant Jozef Handzel in court.  Zachary A. Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Rothstein, Branch 25.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. 
Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible. Defendant states he does not want a public defender. The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 25.
